{"author":{"id":"ae924cad0eccd510bd7c1844896b3dcc00e7daa039003bd9719a515e70528ab9"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1568913922,"nonce":"ibXx7znm7R9SKDOJjlJOui3rt50=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDU6SXNzdWU0OTU5MzA1NjI=","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/2603","origin":"github"},"title":"Robust pipeline for variant calling in viral and bacterial system","message":"Here is an outline of a workflow that needs to be enabled in Galaxy to allow variant calling on HIV-1 datasets\n\n - [ ] Upload all datasets for `PRJNA517147`\n - [ ] QC with `fastqc` and `multiqc`\n - [ ] Clean off Nextera adapters with `trim_galore`\n - [ ] Map read with bwa mem against [K03455.1](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nuccore/K03455.1)\n - [ ] Assess coverage distribution using `samtools depth` and visualize using Jupyter or Galaxy's built in visualization capabilities\n - [ ] Downsample to ~1,000 coverage in order to run `Freebayes` (Freebayes hangs on datasets where coverage if too high). The downsampling is tricky and would be a good test of new workflow functionality as it will require:\n   * [ ] Compute per base depth for every sample using `samtools depth`\n   * [ ] From `samtools depth` compute median depth per sample. This will give one number per sample. \n   * [ ] Using this number we can now calculate downsampling factor for each sample as `F = 1/(median_depth_for_given_sample/1000)`\n   * [ ] Downsampling is only performed for samples where `F \u003c 1`. If `F \u003e= 1` no downsampling is necessary\n - [ ] Calling variants with\n   * [ ] FreeBayes\n   * [ ] Mutect2\n   * [ ] NVC\n - [ ] Normalize and resolve multiallelic sites with `bcftools norm`\n - [ ] Convert VCF into tab-delimited data using `bcftools query`. Here galaxy wrapper for this tools will need to have access to VCF metadata to allow field selection","files":null}]}